<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                    <head>No. 234.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Washburne</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-06-10"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 10,
                            1874</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 616.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                        dispatches numbered 968, 969, 970, and 971.</p>
                    <p>Referring to your No. 968, relating to a convention for the amelioration of
                        the condition of prisoners of war, to be held at Brussels in July next, it
                        does not seem that the United States are called upon to take part
                        therein.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>